  plymouth-quit-wait can prevent the splash from ever being torn down and can wedge
  the graphical/display-manager handoff, so boot appears stuck at the splash and
  never reaches a networked multi-user state (explaining C as downstream of A).
  Proposed fix: stop masking these units (remove the mask, or `systemctl unmask`),
  since DeviceTimeout=8 already bounds the splash.
