codex
One nuance on symptom A: masking `plymouth-quit.service` clearly explains “the splash never tears down,” but by systemd semantics a masked unit wanted by `multi-user.target` should fail its own job rather than hold the target forever. I’m checking the unit relationships before calling the lack of network downstream versus independent.
